  {
    id: 'faq-2',
    title: 'What is the difference between software as a service and outsourcing?',
    answer:
      'SaaS or Software as a Service is a model where software is delivered over the internet, allowing users to access it on a subscription basis without the need for installation or maintenance. Outsourcing, on the other hand, involves hiring an external company to develop, manage, or maintain software for your business, tailored to your specific needs. At WeblineIndia, we offer both SaaS solutions and software outsourcing services. Our SaaS offerings empower businesses with ready-to-use, scalable tools, while our outsourcing services focus on delivering custom software development and maintenance to meet your unique requirements.',
  },
  {
