    id: 'faq-5',
    title: 'What happens when you outsource?',
    answer:
      'When you outsource, you delegate specific business tasks, such as software development or IT management, to an external team or company. This process allows you to access specialized expertise, reduce costs, and focus on core business operations. The outsourcing partner takes responsibility for delivering the agreed-upon services or solutions within the specified timeline and budget. Outsourcing often involves regular communication, progress updates, and collaboration to ensure the project aligns with your goals and expectations. With WeblineIndia, outsourcing becomes a seamless experience. Our proven RelyShore™ model ensures that your projects are managed efficiently by a team of skilled professionals. We handle everything from planning and development to testing and deployment, all while maintaining transparency and delivering high-quality results. With over 26 years of experience, ISO-certified processes, and a commitment to client success, WeblineIndia is your trusted partner for outsourcing.',
